cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MS, cs.MM

This paper involves the development of a fully automated knee MRI segmentation method using a novel hierarchical set of random forests classifiers. The method involves learning the appearance of cartilage regions and their boundaries, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of a layered optimal graph image segmentation of multiple objects and surfaces (LOGISMOS) framework involves optimization and modeling, which can be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and modeling and simulation (cs.MS). Finally, the paper also involves the segmentation of multi-surface and multi-object knee MRI data, which can be categorized under multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
